com.faunadb.client

Class FaunaClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.faunadb.client.FaunaClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    public class FaunaClient
extends Object
implements AutoCloseable
    The Java native client for FaunaDB.

    This client is asynchronous, so all methods that perform latent operations return a ListenableFuture.

    Queries are constructed by using the static helpers in the Language package.

    Example: 

    
 import static com.faunadb.client.query.Language.*;
 FaunaClient client = FaunaClient.builder().withSecret("someAuthToken").build();
 client.query(Get(Ref("some/ref")));
    See Also:
    Language

        public FaunaClient newSessionClient(String secret)
        Creates a session client with the user secret provided. Queries submited to a session client will be authenticated with the secret provided. A session client shares its parent's Connection instance.

      • query

        public ListenableFuture<Value> query(Expr expr)
        Issues a Query to FaunaDB.

        Queries are modeled through the FaunaDB query language, represented by the helper functions in the Language class.

        Responses are modeled as a general response tree. Each node is a Value, and can be coerced to structured types through various methods on that class.

        Parameters:
        expr - The query expression to be sent to FaunaDB.
        Returns:
        A ListenableFuture containing the root node of the Response tree.
        See Also:
        Value, Language

      • query

        public ListenableFuture<ImmutableList<Value>> query(List<? extends Expr> exprs)
        Issues multiple queries to FaunaDB.

        These queries are sent to FaunaDB in a single request, and are evaluated. The list of response nodes is returned in the same order as the issued queries.

        See query(Expr) for more information on the individual queries.

        Parameters:
        exprs - the list of query expressions to be sent to FaunaDB.
        Returns:
        a ListenableFuture containing an ordered list of root response nodes.
